reviews.text: Great place to bring your kids to do a little ocean fishing at a very cheap price. They have low rates for kids and they provide the gear. If you stay on the pier you don't even need a license. Most of the long time fisherman on the pier are super nice and helpful. We met a great guy from New York who was the best. Helpful. Tolerant of kids. My two boys caught sharks and even a stingray. It was awesome and very cheap. Great super memorable experience.
Cool restaurant that is open for breakfast. Try the crab cake Benedict. Great view of the ocean while dining. Service was fast and friendly.
Great place to eat very friendly atmosphere.

I loved this place. Got there as soon as it opened and caught fish all day including crab pompano and a almost 4' nurse shark. And the bait is pretty cheap. 7 dollars to fish plus 7 for a rod (you can bring ur own and not pay that) and like 3 for a good amount of bait. I had a great time and would recommend it to anyone looking to do a little fishing or take there kids fishing. It's a great place.

We visited Crabby Joe's and it was awesome!! We sat outside on the pier. I ordered the Mermaid Fish Ruben and it was incredible, also they have the best pasta salad I have ever had. We loved it so much that we went back 2 days later. Also, you must try the Peanut Butter Pie.

This was our second visit here on 2 different vacations.  The first time was excellent, they were very busy but we still didn't wait long and the food was excellent.  The second time was last week, the last week in February, a weekday.  They weren't as busy, we were seated right away.  The waitress was very nice and good.  My breakfast unfortunately wasn't anywhere near as good as the first time.  I got the eggs Benedict--the eggs were barely warm.  I requested that the breakfast be microwaved to warm it up as I didn't want to wait for a new meal.  This worked well, then I realized that the English muffins hadn't been toasted first.  It made a very noticeable difference in the taste of the meal.  It wasn't bad, just not as good.  We will still probably go back the next time we're down there, I was just a little disappointed in the food quality.  The decorations inside are so cute,  I love all the clever saying on the signs.

Amazing well seasoned breakfast. Plenty food served. Exceptional customer service even one of the owners came by our table and greeted us and asked how was the food. And you cannot beat affordable prices!

It was pretty good. All meat omelet was delish. I ordered hash browns, extra crispy. They were definitely extra crispy but they were also, strangely, very thin. Like 10 sheets of printer paper thin. They were good but weird.

Hands down, best breakfast diner on the east coast... worth the wait during the event weeks.. and a destination for anyone that knows the best... The staff is second to NONE! Owners are onsite, managing and attentive to their loyal customers! A MUST if your in Daytona..

I read the reviews on the fritters and they did not disappoint. Coffee was very good too. Bathroom could have been cleaner and there was a short wait. But the place is packed fir a reason. Good service considering the pace.

Had Crabby Joe’s for the first time. It was very cool eating over the water. What a great night time view of the Daytona Beach Shores skyline. The staff were all very friendly. The food was good. It’s not high end seafood but a very good value in my opinion. We will eat there again for sure. Nice place.
The food was AMAZING! The servants was extremely friendly. Food was served quickly. Can’t forget about the Strawberry/Mango Daiquiri and how delicious it was. It was all well worth it. I LOVE it.

We’ve been going here for years and have always had a great experience, friendly service and delicious food! We mainly go for breakfast and love the fish and eggs! You can’t beat the view, this is where you go when you want to eat at the beach. Go at off times if you don’t want to wait, don’t sit outside if you don’t want the wind, sun and birds (you know, normal things that occur at the beach). The prices fit right in with anywhere else in the area but you’re getting a spectacular view as well. I always recommend going here (as a local) to anyone coming from out of town.

Wonderful beach atmosphere on a small pier. Reasonably priced dishes. Great burgers and seafood. Friendly servers and staff. Make sure you walk through the restaurant to the end of the pier to enjoy the view of the water and the people fishing off the pier.
A good place for a bite. The service was slow but the servers we friendly. The food was good for a beach establishment. The drinks were delicious and not overly priced! I definitely will need back!

This place rocks I wish I could give it 10 stars, but it only goes to five. The service was great and our food was delicious! We loved our waiter Billy! I would highly recommend it and they are family friendly.
I love coming here! Tonight we had the pleasure of dining here with Billy as our server. He made us feel like family and took amazing care of us. The food is always impeccable—save room for dessert!

Every spring break for nine years we have enjoyed the food here. The waiters are amazing, but the ambiance is the best part. The food is also good, also enjoyed with Sinatra playing in the background.
Our dinners were all delicious. Our server was super friendly and attentive. Reasonably priced. A great place for dinner!
Our night here was glorious! We enjoyed a few hours over dinner and wine without feeling rushed or hurried. The meal was delicious and the service was on point. We will definitely be back!

Great restaurant so close and missed by many!
Excellent food and variety!
Pizza yummy! Friendly service and I'll be a repeat customer for sure!

Service was Excellent! We had baked ravioli and New York strip and both were very good. The bread was warm and tasted fresh. The salad is your basic salad which is fine with me. The ranch dressing was good. Decor is dated but the music was from the 80s which we like and it wasn't too loud. We'd eat here again.

Salad was on a small plate, iceberg lettuce with a few sprigs of red cabbage and one thin slice of tomato cut in half. Only 3 choices of dressing.

Coffee is an instant pack like a teabag.

The pork chops were so tough they were hard to cut. I think one was re-nuked from a previous meal. The baked potato was gluey in texture.

The manicotti was unexceptionable but edible. The sauce was very acidic...nothing fresh was included. It was probably out of a jar. No spices were included in the ricotta cheese stuffing.

The bread was warm but tasteless.

The broccoli, while very limited, was cooked well.

Service was good.

We will never return.
Dishes were dirty, food was horrible. Place outdated. And restaurant stinks!  Waitress was nice!

The first issue is being told to seat yourself. This caused us to be basically forgotten. We had to catch someone's eye just to get a menu. Then it went downhill from there. Salads were served but we had no silverware and couldn't catch our waitress eye. The food was tasty but not worth the wait.  Asked for a drink refill to go and got soda instead of tea then had to wait again to get the waitress attention.

This place rocks I wish I could give it 10 stars, but it only goes to five. The service was great and our food was delicious! We loved our waiter Billy! I would highly recommend it and they are family friendly.
I love coming here! Tonight we had the pleasure of dining here with Billy as our server. He made us feel like family and took amazing care of us. The food is always impeccable—save room for dessert!

Every spring break for nine years we have enjoyed the food here. The waiters are amazing, but the ambiance is the best part. The food is also good, also enjoyed with Sinatra playing in the background.
Our dinners were all delicious. Our server was super friendly and attentive. Reasonably priced. A great place for dinner!
Our night here was glorious! We enjoyed a few hours over dinner and wine without feeling rushed or hurried. The meal was delicious and the service was on point. We will definitely be back!

Great food and service. Built in, what was many years ago, a gas station which is why the restrooms are still outside. You can taste the freshness of their food. Love the flavor of the fresh made pizza dough. Good prices and they deliver too. Table service inside but grab your own menu then seat yourself as the signs say.

I ordered a white pizza and garlic knots for delivery and am so happy with my order that I'm writing my review as I eat! The online ordering was simple enough. Being a product of the 90's I was hoping to have some ranch for dipping with my order but couldn't find that as an option. I ended up requesting some in the "notes for delivery" section even though it specifically asks you not to do that. So I was thrilled to see that they had included several with no up charge. 

The delivery man was also very nice, friendly, and respectful. It turns out my hotel won't allow drivers to come directly to the rooms so I had to meet him in the lobby. The order came very promptly and sooner than had been indicated but the driver called to let me know I would need to come downstairs with enough time for me to meet him there. If I was a local this would be my go to spot!
Best homemade pizzeria ever! The cheese they use is the Best! Very home like environment but still business professional. Excellent customer services. Great overall.
Cheese calzone,  pasta, and a gyros...all was great. Prices are great just like the food and lets not forget the beer is cold.. thanks for the wonderful food
Good service and was great pizza. Low key. Cheap drinks. Love it!

What a hidden gem this is!!! The furnishings and atmosphere is a little dated but who cares. Very attentive wait staff, food was amazing which was unexpected. When we first walked in we had our doubts but this will be added to our favorites list. This place is attached to a beat Western inn and I think it is where the inn serves their breakfast. We were there for dinner. I had the BBQ chicken and wife had Rachel Rueben. I could not believe how tender and succulent the chicken was. Fall off the bone tender. Sauce was good. Wife's Rachel Reuben was also excellent. Fish sandwich on rye with a bit of thousand island dressing. Fish was tender, bread was fresh. Honestly could not ask for a better meal. Price was more than fair and wait staff was attentive.

Came here with a large group. Service was prompt and friendly despite being a big group.

I got the shrimp scampi bowl. Was excellent. Most liked their food.. Someone's steak was dry. Someone felt fries were too thick. 

They have a breakfast buffet which is wonderful! Anything one might want..including protein items.

Relaxed and casual atmosphere.

I gotta be real, I didn't expect much from this place. Seriously,  it's in the Best Western. However,  I was so surprised. The food was amazing. We had the sirloin and grilled shrimp.  Delicious.  Service was friendly, and prices are reasonable.  I'd bet you won't be disappointed.
Nice family friendly  menu
A Lovely and Fun Evening. Good Food and played a few games of pool......LOVE IT!!!
